<p class="lead">
    Welcome to my website. I'm a backend Software Engineer with 5+ years of experience designing, building, and operating
    backend services, cloud infrastructure, and web applications serving millions of users. I specialize in system design,
    distributed systems, and infrastructure automation, with an emphasis on clean architecture and long-term
    maintainability. I've worked extensively with technologies such as Azure, Docker, ASP.NET, and Node.js to deliver
    reliable, production-grade systems.
</p>
<p>
    My interest in technology started early. Growing up, I spent much of my time exploring computers and playing video games
    like RuneScape, World of Warcraft, and The Elder Scrolls which sparked a deeper curiosity in technology. That curiosity
    led me to experiment with the command line, scripting, and building computers as a teenager.
</p>
<p>
    I went on to study Computer Science at Temple University, where I developed a strong foundation in software engineering
    principles, algorithms, and system design. After graduating, I began my career at a consulting firm, where I delivered
    solutions across public, private, and higher education sectors. This experience required quickly understanding complex
    domains, navigating diverse codebases, and making effective engineering decisions in a variety of environments.
</p>
<p>
    Outside of work, I spend time gaming, modding, and contributing to open-source projects. I also have a strong interest
    in philosophy and history, particularly ancient history, and enjoy exploring science fiction and fantasy worlds like The
    Lord of the Rings, Warcraft, Warhammer, and Dune.
</p>